The paper deals with the problem of object segmentation in depth maps for robotic grasping, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a fully convolutional network for object segmentation, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning and synthetic data, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of edge detection and contour-oriented loss functions, which are relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR).
